===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₂ent-|*swer-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|answere}}, {{m|enm|andsware}}, from {{inh|en|ang|andswaru||answer}}, from {{confix|ang|and|t1=against|swaru|t2=affirmation|nocat=1}}, (from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₂ent-||front, forehead}} and {{der|en|ang|swerian||to swear}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*swer-}}), suggesting an original meaning of "a sworn statement rebutting a charge". The cognates suggest the existence of {{der|en|gem-pro|*andswara-||a reply to a question}}. Cognate with {{cog|ofs|ondser||answer}}, {{cog|osx|andswōr||answer}}, {{cog|da|-}} and {{cog|sv|ansvar||liability, responsibility, answer}}, {{cog|is|andsvar||answer, response}}. Compare also {{cog|ang|andwyrde||answer}} (cognate to {{cog|nl|antwoord}}, {{cog|de|Antwort}}), {{cog|ang|andcwiss||reply}}, {{cog|de|Schwur||oath, vow}}.

